    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Can we also change `api` to not nest it's options within the `rest` subcategory?\r\nCurrently, we are required to configure `api` options like this:\r\n```\r\n\"api\": {\r\n    \"rest\": {\r\n      \"enabled\": true,\r\n      \"namespaces\": [\"beacon\", \"validator\"],\r\n      \"host\": \"127.0.0.1\",\r\n      \"port\": 9596,\r\n      \"cors\": {\r\n        \"origin\": \"*\"\r\n      }\r\n    }\r\n  },\r\n```\r\n\r\nbut i think we should structure them like this:\r\n```\r\n  \"api\": {\r\n    \"enabled\": true,\r\n    \"namespaces\": [\"beacon\", \"validator\"],\r\n    \"host\": \"127.0.0.1\",\r\n    \"port\": 9596,\r\n    \"cors\": {\r\n      \"origin\": \"*\"\r\n    }\r\n  },\r\n```",
